                      "data": "{\"medication\":\"Metformin\",\"infoType\":\"SideEffects\",\"information\":\"Common side effects include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, and stomach pain, especially when starting the medication. These often improve over time. Take with food to reduce stomach upset. Rare but serious: lactic acidosis — seek immediate medical attention if you experience unusual muscle pain, difficulty breathing, or stomach pain with nausea. Always consult your prescribing physician before making any changes to your medication regimen.\",\"disclaimer\":\"This information is for general educational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional medical advice. Always follow your doctor's instructions.\"}",
                      "error": ""
                    }
                  }
                }
